## TL;DR: What Every 5ct Cushion Buyer Must Know First

The 5 carat cushion cut diamond ring is the size where the diamond market bifurcates completely. Natural 5ct GIA cushion diamonds exist in retail — seven stones on Blue Nile — but entry starts at $71,271 and reaches $177,928, making this a market that is theoretically open but practically accessible only to buyers who have decided, before searching, that natural origin at six-figure prices is non-negotiable. Lab-grown cushions at 5ct start at $10,157 for an IGI D-VVS1, and this is where The Lab Sovereign concept defines the market: at 5ct, IGI-certified lab cushions are the only product that exists at scale, at reasonable price, and in inventory depth.

**Contrarian Truth — The Lab Sovereign:** At 5ct, GIA-certified lab cushions exist — but they cost $39,959–$57,123. IGI-certified lab cushions start at $10,157. The $29,000–$47,000 gap between GIA and IGI lab cushions at 5ct is not primarily a quality difference; it is a market structure difference. GIA's conservative grading of lab-grown diamonds means fewer 5ct lab stones achieve GIA's D-VVS1 threshold, creating scarcity and premium pricing for GIA lab at this size. IGI's grading is well-recognised in the lab-grown market, accepted by major jewellers and insurers, and delivers a stone that is chemically identical to the GIA-certified alternative at $29,000 less. At 5ct, IGI is not a compromise — it is the sovereign of the accessible lab market.

**Live price snapshot (Blue Nile {{year}}):**
- Lab 5ct IGI D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified: **[$10,157](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27641932?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Lab 5ct IGI D-IF Ideal Cushion Modified: **[$30,186](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29038942?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Natural 5ct GIA G-VS1 Ideal Cushion Modified: **[$71,271](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/18306815?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**

**→ The best entry point** for lab buyers is the [IGI 5ct D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified at $10,157](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27641932?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — top colour, VVS1 clarity, Ideal cut, 11mm face-up impact, and a price that makes a 5ct cushion ring achievable at a total cost under $12,000. For buyers who specifically require GIA certification at 5ct lab: the [GIA 4.95ct E-IF Ideal at $39,959](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27493672?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the GIA entry, at four times the IGI price. For natural buyers who have examined and committed to natural origin at this size: the [GIA 5.05ct G-VS1 Ideal at $71,271](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/18306815?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the only natural 5ct cushion entry under $100,000.

