## What Is a 5 Carat Cushion Cut Diamond Ring?

A 5 carat cushion cut diamond ring centres a 5ct cushion-shaped diamond — approximately 11mm × 11mm in standard square proportions — in an engagement ring setting. At 5ct, the cushion cut reaches a face-up area of approximately 121mm², 50% larger than a 3ct cushion and 21% larger than a 4ct cushion. The 5ct cushion on the hand is not merely a large diamond ring; it occupies the finger from knuckle to knuckle on most hands, reads as a statement from across a room, and is virtually never seen in everyday retail environments.

I'm **Farzana Hasan**, a GIA Expert. The [5 carat cushion cut](/cushion-cut-diamond) sits at the intersection of the most extreme expressions of every trend in the cushion market: The Empty Tier reaches its logical endpoint in the natural segment, The Lab Sovereign establishes IGI as the dominant certification at the accessible lab price point, The Crushed Ice Trap is at maximum intensity at 11mm face-up, and The Pillow Premium — the cushion's systematic cost premium over other shapes — becomes irrelevant in the natural market because the entire 5ct natural segment is already a premium-only tier.

What matters most at 5ct: understanding that the natural and lab markets operate on completely different logic at this size, understanding The Lab Sovereign's implication (IGI is the correct certification for most lab 5ct buyers, not a compromise), and understanding that the 5ct face-up area makes every quality, setting, and aesthetic decision more consequential than at any smaller size. Buyers who treated the 2ct or 3ct purchase as a careful but manageable decision face a qualitatively different exercise at 5ct — one where the physical scale of the stone, the scarcity of the natural market, and the certification dynamics of the lab market all demand clear-headed analysis before any purchase commitment.

For context on how the market escalates to 5ct, the [4 carat cushion cut diamond ring guide](/4-carat-cushion-cut-diamond-ring) documents The Empty Tier's origin and the trajectory from 3ct through 4ct natural pricing.

Full credentials and methodology at **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**.

